component 0: [["Hello", "Hi, I am Raggy, your personal tech chatbot. Ask my anything about tech, from programming languages, machine learning to natural language processing, I'll be here to help :)"]]
[["When is Python released?", "Python was first released in 1991 as Python 0.9.0.  Python 2.0 was released in 2000.  Starting with Python 3.9, major releases are expected to happen annually. \n"]]

[["What are the core concepts of AI?", "The core concepts of AI are complex and debated. Some consider the ability to learn and adapt as central, while others focus on problem-solving and decision-making.  The field encompasses a wide range of techniques, including machine learning, deep learning, and natural language processing. \n"]]

[["What is ML?", "ML stands for Machine Learning. It is a type of artificial intelligence that allows computers to learn from data without being explicitly programmed. ML algorithms can be used to solve a wide range of problems, including natural language processing, computer vision, and speech recognition. \n"]]
